INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY BOMBAY

Powai, Mumbai – 400076

Advertisement No. I-20/2022-23

Walk-in-Selection Process

 

Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, an Institute of National importance adjudged as Institute of Eminence, is looking for a qualified and experienced candidate to be engaged as Temporary Part Time Pre-primary Teacher at IIT-B KG School. The post is temporary, initially for a period of 1 year, to be continued further subject to satisfactory performance. The requisite qualification(s) & experience for the said post are as follows:

Name of the Post               :    Temporary Part Time Pre-primary Teacher

 

No. of Position(s)               :    1 UR

 


Qualification & Experience:    

Senior Secondary (10+2 or equivalent) from a recognized board with at least 50% marks, with    

a)  Diploma in Nursery Teacher Education / Pre-School Education / Early Childhood Education

(DECEd) or equivalent of a duration not less than two years  and having competence to teach 

in Hindi / English. 

Desirable: Teaching experience of five years after passing (10+2).      

                               OR

b) Graduate degree with Diploma in Early Childhood Care and Education 

(ECCEd) or equivalent of a duration not less than one year and having 

competence to teach in Hindi / English.

Desirable: Teaching experience of three years after passing the diploma.                                                

                                               .                     

 Working Hrs                     :     30 hrs / week


Tenure of appointment      :    1 year

                                               (Terminable by 1 month's notice from either sides)


Pay Details                       :     Level EA2 (22000 - 35200)* with one additional annual

                                               increment to the initial basic pay (on pro rata basis).

                                               *(Salary revision is under consideration).


Age limit                          :        Maximum age limit 50 years.

 

Willing and eligible candidates who possess the requisite qualification and experience as mentioned above, are requested to appear for a Walk-in-Selection Process at IIT-B KG School, Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, Powai, Mumbai-400 076, on 17/11/2022 at 10.00 a.m. along with resume, self attested copies of all certificates with originals.

Date:11/11/2022                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               

REGISTRAR

Name of the Post              :     Temporary Part Time Pre-primary (Special Education) Teacher

 

No. of Position(s)               :    1 UR

 

Qualification & Experience:     

Required Qualification:

1. Senior Secondary (10+2 or equivalent) from a recognized board with at least 50% marks 

or a Grauate degree from a recognised university.

                                                                      AND

2. Diploma in special education (minimum duration of one year) from a recognized Institute.


Desirable: Qualification & Experience:

Diploma in Nursery Teacher Education / Pre-School Education / Early Childhood Education 

(DECEd) or equivalent of a duration not less than two years after passing (10+2) and having 

competence to teach in Hindi / English.

Diploma in Early Childhood Care and Education (ECCEd) or equivalent of a duration not less 

than one year after graduation and having competence to teach in Hindi / English.


Working Hrs                     :       30 hrs / week


Tenure of appointment      :      1 year

                                                  (Terminable by 1 month's notice from either sides)


Pay Details                       :     Level EA2 (22000 - 35200)* with one additional annual

                                               increment to the initial basic pay (on pro rata basis).

                                               *(Salary revision is under consideration).


Age limit                          :        Maximum age limit 50 years.

 

Willing and eligible candidates who possess the requisite qualification and experience as mentioned above, are requested to appear for a Walk-in-Selection Process at IIT-B KG School, Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, Powai, Mumbai-400 076, on 17/11/2022 at 10.00 a.m. along with resume, self attested copies of all certificates with originals.

Date:11/11/2022

INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY BOMBAY

Powai, Mumbai – 400076


Advertisement No.: HR-I(HRM-II)/Apprenticeship/August/2022


ENGAGEMENT OF GRADUATE HOLDERS IN NON-TECHNICAL (GENERAL STREAM) AREAS FOR ONE YEAR APPRENTICESHIP TRAINING AT IIT BOMBAY FOR THE YEAR 2022-23 UNDER THE PROVISIONS OF THE APPRENTICES ACT-1961 (AMENDED TILL DATE)

 

Under the provisions of The Apprentices Act-1961 (amended till date), it is proposed to provide practical on-job training for a period of one year to Graduateswho have completed their graduation in the Arts, Commerce, Business Administration, Management Science, Business Studies and passed the qualifying exam after April 2020.

The vacancies are as follows:

Category

No. of seats

SC

2

ST

1

OBC (NCL)

7

Total

10

Total number of apprentice positions : 10

RESERVATION : as per The Apprentices Act-1961 (amended till date).

STIPEND : The Graduate Apprentices will be paid a consolidated stipend of Rs. 9,000/- p. m.

PRESCRIBED QUALIFICATION, ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA, AGE-LIMITS :

(1) Any Indian Citizen with a Degree in Arts, Commerce, Business Administration, Management Science, Business Studies from a recognized University can apply for the post of Graduate Apprentice. The gap between the last date of application and the passing date of the qualifying degree examination should not be more than 2 years

(2) Candidates who have already registered / undergone / undergoing apprenticeship training under Apprentices Act elsewhere are not eligible to apply.

(3) The minimum age of the candidate should be between 18 to 25 years as on the day of application. A relaxation in upper age limit is applicable as per the Govt. of India guidelines for SC / ST / OBC (NCL).

SELECTION PROCESS

(1) All candidates have to upload their final marks in percentage only and NOT in CGPA.
